 &quot;make up&quot; the time they didn't have to work on their product.<br><br>Verant is absolutely terrible at reading the pulse of their players, it just takes another company's willingness to solve end game problems and some players who are willing to not have as many zones while their new game ages some. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uzozz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zozz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dead Gnome</span><br>  Posts: 607<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 1:10:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2265.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> I like Dungeon Siege. <br><br>I didn't read the review, or the reviews of the reviews. <br><br>I've been playing it lately and it's a pretty solid game. <br>The user interface is very intuitive and the game seems to have been designed with a geat attention to detail. <br>It has some elements that are similar to D2, but overall it is a much more robust game.  <br>It looks nice, it plays smooth.  No loading screens(which is really hard to get used to believe it or not).<br><br>Character development is proactive and passive at the same time (which is frustrating as heck, sometimes).  My character is the wimpiest in my party because he has all balanced skills at the moment (melee 2  range 2 combat magic 2 nature magic 2) while my other characters that I have been less conscious of (ie. I haven't been micromanaging them now that I have a large party like I was doing when my character was solo) have all specialized and are much more useful in their niches I don't want to change them to do different skills now.<br><br>Multiplayer is something that I haven't tried yet, so I can' really comment on how that works out.  I am probably going to try it out on my LAN sometime in the next few days.<br><br>I am not very far into the game, but I would recommend getting it if the single player fantasy genre appeals to you at all.  The designer is committed to releasing a world editing tool and exteensive mod support, so this title and it's successive incarnations are going to be around in one form or another for a long time. <br><br>Zozz<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usotae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sotae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 451<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 4:33:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2265.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> zozz damnit... e-mail me!<br><br>kasler@filertel.com <br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>we'll play some multiplayer DS~ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ulethav.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lethav</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/2/02 5:16:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2265.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/file.aspx/path=/Lethav/fullsize/letha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: well</span><hr size=1> DS has to be first 3d game 